#WannaCry Ransomware Attack

What Happened?
WannaCry was a ransomware attack that occurred in May 2017. The malware spread rapidly across computers worldwide by exploiting a vulnerability in Microsoft Windows systems. Once a computer was infected, the ransomware encrypted files and demanded payment in Bitcoin to restore access.
The attack affected organizations, businesses, hospitals, and government agencies in more than 150 countries.

Which Part of the CIA Triad Was Affected?
Availability
The primary CIA Triad component affected was Availability. Users were unable to access their files and systems because the ransomware encrypted the data.
Integrity
Integrity was also affected because files were modified and encrypted without the owner's permission.


What Was the Impact?
•	Thousands of computers were infected worldwide.
•	Hospitals in the United Kingdom had to cancel appointments and medical procedures.
•	Businesses experienced operational disruptions.
•	Organizations suffered financial losses and downtime.
•	Important files became inaccessible until systems were restored.

How Could It Have Been Prevented?
The attack could have been prevented by:
1.	Regularly updating operating systems and installing security patches.
2.	Using antivirus and endpoint protection software.
3.	Creating regular backups of important data.
4.	Avoiding suspicious email attachments and links.
5.	Implementing strong cybersecurity awareness training for employees.
6.	Keeping network security systems properly configured and updated.
